know as the Iliad and the Odyssey. Sure to challenge orthodox views and provoke lively debate, Nagy's book will be essential reading for all students of oral traditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aEpic poetry, GreekxHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aOral traditionzGreece. 0aOral-formulaic analysis. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/75561140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292796218423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292796218/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK